ClipScribe Alembic migrations.

Run from backend/:

    uv run alembic upgrade head

The Alembic environment resolves the active database URL through
src.db.engine.resolve_database_url(), so migrations target the same SQLite or
PostgreSQL database configured for the application.

Use `upgrade head` to apply existing migrations. Use `revision --autogenerate`
only when authoring a new migration after updating `backend/src/db/schema.py`;
review the generated file before committing it. Production deploys should run
the same migration step before starting API or worker processes.
